               <p>FRANCIS WEEDON. On the 30th of July I was in <placeName id="t18270913-195-crimeloc1101">Goswell-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-195-crimeloc1101" type="placeName" value="Goswell-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-195-crimeloc1101" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-195-off1099 t18270913-195-crimeloc1101"></join>, with my wife, about half-past eight o'clock in the evening; she said she felt something at her arm - I felt my pocket, and my handkerchief was gone, which I had used within an hour. I saw two boys go by at the instant, but I cannot identify them - Roe immediately came up, and asked if I had lost any thing; he said, if I would follow him, he thought he could find the persons who had it; we went on; he turned a corner, and took Stevens - I followed him, and took hold of Stratford - I saw Stevens drop my handkerchief from his pocket - I took it up, and put it into my pocket; there were no other persons round at that time.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-195-person1796">
                  JOHN 
                  ROE
               <interp inst="t18270913-195-person1796" type="surname" value="ROE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-195-person1796" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-195-person1796" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was in Goswell-street, and saw the prisoners, with two others, following this gentleman and lady; and saw the gentleman feeling his pocket - I asked if he had lost any thing; he said he had - I went on to Turk's Head-court, and found the two prisoners; the witness caught hold of Stratford - I am quite sure they were with two others whom I had seen altogether just before.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-195-person1797">
                  JAMES 
                  FORDHAM
               <interp inst="t18270913-195-person1797" type="surname" value="FORDHAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-195-person1797" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-195-person1797" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I received the prisoner, at the watch-house, and produce the handkerchief, which I received from Mr. Weedon.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
